  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through multiple approaches, including:\n\n1. Legislative frameworks\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- International cooperation agreements\n\n2. Law enforcement strategies\n- Financial investigation units\n- Tracking suspicious financial transactions\n- Collaboration between domestic and international agencies\n- Advanced forensic accounting techniques\n\n3. Regulatory oversight\n- Financial institution compliance requirements\n- Regular audits and inspections\n- Penalties for non-compliance\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious activities\n\n4. Technological tools\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Data analysis software\n- Digital forensics\n- Blockchain tracking capabilities\n\n5. Criminal prosecution\n- Specialized financial crime prosecutors\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Potential imprisonment\n\nThese approaches work together to detect, prevent, and prosecute sophisticated money laundering operations across different jurisdictions.",
